{"title_page": "Abdus Salam (general)", "text_new": "{{Infobox officeholder\n| name = Abdus Salam\n| office = Member of Bangladesh Parliament\n| term_start = \n| term_end = \n| predecessor = \n| successor = \n| birth_date = \n| birth_place = \n| death_date = \n| death_place = \n| party = [[Bangladesh Awami League]]\n| bodyclass = \n| mainwidth = \n}}\n'''Abdus Salam''' is a [[Bangladesh Awami League]] politician, retired Major General, and the former Member of Parliament of [[Mymensingh-11]].\n\n==Career==\nAhmed was elected to parliament from Mymensingh-11 as a Bangladesh Awami League candidate in 2008. His nomination was cancelled by the [[Bangladesh Election Commission]] for defaulting on a loan. He appealed the cancellation and was subsequently elected during the appeal process. In 2013, Bangladesh High Court cancelled his election following an appeal by an Awami League activists.<ref>{{cite news |title=Mymensingh-9 MP disqualified |url=https://bdnews24.com/bangladesh/2013/11/22/mymensingh-9-mp-disqualified |accessdate=9 October 2019 |work=bdnews24.com}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thedailystar.net/news/hc-declares-abdus-salams-js-membership-illegal|title=HC declares Abdus Salam's JS membership illegal|date=2013-11-22|website=The Daily Star|language=en|access-date=2019-10-09}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Ahmed}}\n[[Category:Bangladesh Awami League politicians]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:9th Jatiya Sangsad members]]\n[[Category:Bangladesh Army generals]]\n\n\n{{Bangladesh-politician-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox officeholder\n| name = Abdus Salam\n| office = Member of Bangladesh Parliament\n| term_start = \n| term_end = \n| predecessor = \n| successor = \n| birth_date = \n| birth_place = \n| death_date = \n| death_place = \n| party = [[Bangladesh Awami League]]\n| bodyclass = \n| mainwidth = \n}}\n'''Abdus Salam''' is a [[Bangladesh Awami League]] politician, retired Major General, and the former Member of Parliament of [[Mymensingh-11]].\n\n==Career==\nAhmed was elected to parliament from Mymensingh-11 as a Bangladesh Awami League candidate in 2008. His nomination was cancelled by the [[Bangladesh Election Commission]] for defaulting on a loan. He appealed the cancellation and was subsequently elected during the appeal process. In 2013, Bangladesh High Court cancelled his election following an appeal by an Awami League activists.<ref>{{cite news |title=Mymensingh-9 MP disqualified |url=https://bdnews24.com/bangladesh/2013/11/22/mymensingh-9-mp-disqualified |accessdate=9 October 2019 |work=bdnews24.com}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thedailystar.net/news/hc-declares-abdus-salams-js-membership-illegal|title=HC declares Abdus Salam's JS membership illegal|date=2013-11-22|website=The Daily Star|language=en|access-date=2019-10-09}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Ahmed}}\n[[Category:Bangladesh Awami League politicians]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:9th Jatiya Sangsad members]]\n[[Category:Bangladesh Army generals]]\n\n\n{{Bangladesh-politician-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Rfl0216", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Abdus_Salam_(general)"}
